OL,3,CDedicated Newsnight in-depth
OL,4,Cjournalism: luxury BBC can no longer
OL,5,Cafford
OL,7,FShould other BBC services or
OL,8,Fprogrammes face the chop instead?
OL,10,FIt's easy to argue that certain
OL,11,Fpopular TV programmes or Radio 1 and 2
OL,12,Fdo not deserve public money while the
OL,13,Fmarket alone would never provide
OL,14,FNewsnight or English local radio. But
OL,15,Fhuge numbers of people enjoy these
OL,16,Fprogrammes and services.
OL,18,FUltimately it is an impossible circle
OL,19,Fto square. The very point of a
OL,20,Fpublicly funded broadcaster is that it
OL,21,Fdoes important things which may not
OL,22,Fmake commercial sense.
